        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 14:37:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nI see that *.js files under vid-app-common are not counted for lines.\nIt is pretty visible comparing these two pages:\n\n[1] https://sonar.onap.org/code?id=org.onap.vid%3Avid-parent&selected=org.onap.vid%3Avid-app-common%3Asrc%2Fmain%2Fwebapp%2Fapp%2Fvid%2Fscripts%2Fcontroller\n[2] https://sonarcloud.io/code?id=onap_vid&selected=onap_vid%3Avid-app-common%2Fsrc%2Fmain%2Fwebapp%2Fapp%2Fvid%2Fscripts%2Fcontroller\n\nSee that in [2], there are no lines of code.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "7b72a0d9d8ef9344dce2a0ff027b593497248e0c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 18:13:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThanks for reviewing Ittay,Since we do not have control of the plugins in SonarCloud anymore, I had reached out to Sonar team for help since clamp was facing a similar issue. \nThey replied with something like this for them \"\"When I check the analysis on SonarCloud it looks like target/ui-react/src directory is not indexed by SQ at all. That could explain the difference in coverage, you should understand why this directory is not included anymore.\" \"\n\nI am still trying to understand if we need to explicitly point the reports somehow but i am still investigating. \n\nYou know anything about it?",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "d31b0c69a4ffe48eb906645ec39b5c277d98bb8c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4379,
          "name": "Ittay Stern",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ittay.stern@att.com",
          "username": "ittays"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-25 12:53:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> Thanks for reviewing Ittay,Since we do not have control of the plugins in SonarCloud anymore, I had reached out to Sonar team for help since clamp was facing a similar issue. \n> They replied with something like this for them \"\"When I check the analysis on SonarCloud it looks like target/ui-react/src directory is not indexed by SQ at all. That could explain the difference in coverage, you should understand why this directory is not included anymore.\" \"\n> \n> I am still trying to understand if we need to explicitly point the reports somehow but i am still investigating. \n> \n> You know anything about it?\n\nfrom my POV, it is ok to migrate, and handle this issue separately.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
